			Taking a nice warm bath can be very soothing, but for people with mobility related problems, a relaxing bath can be very stressful and dangerous. Having the proper safety equipment at home for an elderly or a disabled person is very important to make them feel secure and give them some independence. A bath tub chair lift can allow them to once again enjoy the comfort of a warm bath.
<br />; 
<br />;Bathroom: Hazardous for those with Mobility Problems
<br />; 
<br />;Whether it involves bathing in the tub or taking a shower, bathroom is a dangerous place for those who are physically challenged.
<br />; 
<br />;Because it is low to the ground, entering and exiting the bathtub is difficult. You have to lean on the wall and the tub edges so you can sit on it and stand once you are done bathing. Those who refuse to use the bathtub take showers instead, which is also dangerous and can result to fall. The tub floor is very slippery that when you fall, serious injury is possible. Besides the bathtub, the shiny floors, water, and electrical appliances in the bathroom add to the hazards.
<br />; 
<br />;Bath Lifts: Practical Solutions for Bathroom Hazards
<br />; 
<br />;Even if you hire someone to take care of your elder or disabled relative, investing in a bath lift is very helpful.
<br />; 
<br />;Bath lifts are medical equipment for the home used to lower and raise an individual into and from the bathtub. These specially designed seats fit into a standard bathtub with no drilling, screwing, or remodeling necessary. Easily movable, you can bring this with you when visiting relatives or going on vacation.
<br />; 
<br />;Users can experience again a comfortable bath using Aquatec Beluga Bath Tub Chair Lift. It has a comfortable seating surface and a reclining backrest for additional comfort. This practical lift chair for bathtubs allows your elders to get in and out of the tub easily and painlessly. This scissor-style device has a durable frame that can lower you to 2.5 inches from the bottom of the tub.
<br />; 
<br />;The machine is run by lithium-ion rechargeable batteries. The batteries can lift the user up to 22 times before it becomes discharged. Getting stuck will not be a problem in case it runs out of power; it will lower the user only if it recognizes that it has enough power to lift the user once he or she is finished bathing. The reclining backrest gives comfort and allows for easy hair rinsing to the user.
<br />; 
<br />;Since almost all models of bathtub chair lifts need not screwing or drilling, powerful suction cups are included in the design to secure the chair to the tub's floor.
<br />; 
<br />;You can choose from several models. If your tub is smaller, or if the person who will use the chair is heavier, there are options available for you.
